ultanas, egg, salt and pepper. Stir mixture with aid of spatula, then mix <b>20 sec\/\/speed 3<b>."},{"content":"Cook <b>2 min\/100°C\/\/speed <b>. Transfer into an ovenproof dish (30 x 21 cm) and smooth top with spatula. Rinse and dry mixing bowl."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Egg topping"},{"content":"Place eggs, salt, pepper and reserved milk into mixing bowl and blend <b>15 sec\/speed 6<b>. Pour over meat mixture and leave to stand for 10 minutes."},{"content":"Arrange bay leaves over top of egg mixture, then bake for 45 minutes (180°C) or until egg mixture has set. Serve with sides of choice."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Bobotie is typically served with yellow rice, apricot chutney and a green salad.","For added flavour, add slivered almonds to the egg topping before baking.","Bobotie is a delicious fusion of the Dutch and Malay culinary influences from the mid-1600s. It's a spicy, slightly sweet mince dish with an eggy custard topping."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h 30m","6 portions"]}